# Engine & Realtime

## GameEngine

- Owns `Board`, `RuleEngine`, `RealTimeArbiter`, and `gameOver` flag
- Public API: `setup`, `requestMove`, `requestJump`, `wait`, `snapshot`, `activeMotions`, `activeRests`, `isGameOver`
- `setup(Board)`: takes an already-parsed board; the engine never parses text. Text → `Board` is `io/BoardParser`'s job (invoked by the composition root)
- `requestMove` / `requestJump`: validate via `RuleEngine`, then delegate motion to arbiter
- Concurrency: a color is blocked while its own piece is in flight (`move_in_flight`). Opposite colors may travel concurrently. A stationary jump (`from == to`) does not occupy a travel route
- Per-piece rest: after landing, a piece must rest before moving/jumping again (`piece_resting`). Travel → long rest (`kLongRestMs`); jump → short rest (`kShortRestMs`)
- `snapshot()`: build immutable `GameSnapshot` for view — no live references to internal state
- Rest/motion for the view: `activeRests()` / `activeMotions()` return DTO vectors (`RestView`, `MotionView`)

```cpp
struct MoveOutcome { bool is_accepted; std::string reason; };
```

## Realtime

- `Motion`: in-flight piece move with `arrivalTime` on game clock
- `Rest`: post-arrival cooldown keyed by cell (`RestKind::Short` / `RestKind::Long`)
- `RealTimeArbiter::advanceTime(ms, board)`: advance clock, expire rests, resolve arrivals, mutate board on landing, start rest for the landed piece
- Returns `std::vector<ArrivalEvent>` for pieces that arrived this tick

## Separation

- Engine coordinates; arbiter handles timing physics
- Rules layer decides legality **before** motion starts
- Capture resolution happens at arrival time, not at move request time
- No stdin/stdout, no pixel coordinates — only grid `Position` values

## Exception handling

### GameEngine

- `requestMove` / `requestJump`: **catch** unexpected errors → `MoveResult{ false, "runtime_error" }`; do not log here
- `setup` / `wait` / `snapshot`: **propagate** exceptions (negative `ms` throws `std::invalid_argument`)
- Never parse text or write to streams in this layer

### RealTimeArbiter

- Validate piece tokens and coordinates; **throw** on violation — no try-catch
- `advanceTime` throws on negative `ms`; board mutations rely on validated `Board` access
